race.comment: RUIN ART (1) produced an impressive win last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 1.3 lengths (30.75) at this track. Looks to have an edge on most of these. WEATHER REPORT (7) turned in a slick 21.85 despite finishing fourth in a Grade 5 at this track last start. This tougher but looks a leading chance. JOSH'S JET (2) had the drop on the pace early but forged to the lead on the bend and drew clear to score (25.78) at this track in a Grade 5 over 457m. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Should feature again. HARA'S TREVOR (8) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.

runners.name: Ayrton Herrera
